== Costume 3 Patch ==
* Costume 3 released for the original 18 characters
<br>

== '''Universal Changes''' ==
* '''Wakeup Input Buffer'''
** Increased 4f → 7f
** Fixed an issue related to buffered inputs that occur immediately after the screen freeze of the opponent's {{clr|SA|Super Art}}
* '''Perfect Parry'''
** Fixed issue where certain actions would shorten the invincibility window on a successful Perfect Parry
* '''Assist Combos (Modern)'''
** Fixed issue that caused the start of the input buffer to occur 1 frame later than intended
** Also fixes issue where Chun-Li and Kimberly could not perform a jump cancel during Assist Combos if a button was input on the same frame
* '''Taunts'''
** Can no longer kara-cancel a special move into a taunt (e.g. PPP~KKK on consecutive frames)
<br>

== '''Key Character Changes''' ==

=== '''A.K.I.''' ===
* {{clr|H|2HK}}
** No longer hits low on active frames 2-5
* {{clr|H|Chi Wen}} ({{clr|H|6HP}})
** Fixed issue where recovery was 1 frame longer on Perfect Parry
* {{clr|L|LP Serpent Lash}} ({{clr|L|236LP}})
** Fixed issue where recovery was 6 frames longer on Perfect Parry
* {{clr|OD|OD Cruel Fate}} ({{clr|OD|214KK}})
** Fixed issue where command inputs would swap directions immediately after jumping over the opponent
* Modern Controls:
** {{clr|M|MP Serpent Lash}} ({{clr|M|236M}}): Fixed issue where inputting Down after a successful command input would prevent the move from coming out
** {{clr|M|MK Snake Step}} ({{clr|DR|5S}}): Fixed issue where this move would be performed with more shortcut commands besides {{clr|DR|5S}}
** {{clr|OD|OD Snake Step}} (A[{{clr|DR|5S}}]): After regular/{{clr|OD|OD}} Nightshade Pulse, the dash no longer comes out while holding any Back/Down/Forward direction
*** Allows A.K.I. to input Modern shortcut moves during the projectile recovery without buffering an accidental {{clr|OD|OD Snake Step}}
<br> 

=== '''Blanka''' ===
* {{clr|H|5HP}}
** Fixed issue where recovery was 5 frames longer on Parry / Perfect Parry / Armor absorb
* {{clr|M|Rock Crusher}} ({{clr|M|6MP}})
** When the opponent is in Burnout, opponent's Drive Gain on Block adjusted 1250,1250 → 1250,625
** Only applies when both hits connect; 2nd hit only builds 1250 Drive gauge for opponent on block during Burnout
* {{clr|SA|SA2}} ({{clr|SA|214214P}})
** Fixed issue where Drive Gauge recovery was different while the install timer was active
** On Ground, Drive Regen per Frame: 50 → 40
** Airborne + Burnout, Drive Regen per Frame: 10 → 20
* {{clr|SA|SA2 Install}} Bug Fixes
** {{clr|L|5LK}} / {{clr|L|2LP}}: fixed issue where front hurtbox during startup was vulnerable to the opponent's cross-up attacks
** {{clr|M|5MK}} / {{clr|H|5HP}}: fixed issue where the special cancel buffer timing was earlier than usual
** {{clr|M|2MP}}: fixed issue where foot hurtbox was smaller than usual
** {{clr|M|j.MP}}: fixed issue where collision box would not expand on hit
** {{clr|OD|[4]6PP}} / [2]8K/{{clr|OD|KK}}: fixed issue where the input buffer for {{clr|SA|Rolling Cannon}} follow-ups did not work
** {{clr|H|[4]6HP}}: fixed issue where bounce-back distance was shorter on Perfect Parry
** {{clr|OD|63214KK}}: fixed issue where the first hit's active frames were 2 frames shorter than usual
<br>

